==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Doter
<hw>Dot"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
dotes; a man whose understanding is enfeebled by age; a dotard.</def>
<rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One excessively fond, or weak in love.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dotery</ent>⟦br⟧
